<HEAD>Red Cross Evacuates 29 Wounded Guerrillas From El Salvador</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delegates of the International Committee of the
Red Cross evacuated 29 wounded and disabled Salvadoran rebels to
Cuba this week, the humanitarian agency announced.
   The guerrillas were airlifted out of El Salvador Wednesday in an
Red Cross-chartered plane, the latest such action under an
agreement between rival sides in the country's civil war, the Red
Cross said in a statement Friday.
   Last year, the all-Swiss organization, which acts as neutral
intermediary in times of conflict, evacuated 157 wounded guerrillas
from El Salvador.
