<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Politics-Quotes     05-07 0268</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Politics-Quotes,250</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, on whether Attorney General Edwin Meese is a
campaign liability: ``I know him well, favorably, but I must say I
am troubled by some of the allegations. I think fair play dictates
that the system go forward and make the determination.''
   
   BUSH, speaking at a Republican dinner in Nebraska about
Democrats Jesse Jackson and Michael Dukakis: ``It's a pleasure to
be here. And I'll be back. And I'm not going to be out-hustled by
the hustler from Chicago or from that traditional liberal Democrat
from Massachusetts.''
   
   MARLIN FITZWATER, White House spokesman, saying it was
courageous for Bush to refrain from making recommendations to
President Reagan during cabinet meetings:``He has for the first
time in history defined the vice presidency in a way that is
meaningful to the president and has made it the confidential
adviser that I think is very important; and I suspect future vice
presidents will want to follow that mold.''
   
   BILL CLINTON, governor of Arkansas, coalescing with five
governors of mostly Western states in endorsing Michael Dukakis for
the Democratic presidential nomination: ``Gov. Dukakis has emerged
as the voters' choice, the clear leader in the Democratic
nomination process. It is time for the party leadership to unite
behind his candidacy.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, on front-runner Dukakis and other obstacles that
he says stand between himself and the Democratic nomination:``The
press, the pundits, the party, the candidate _ it's not just me and
him; it's me and them.''
</TEXT>
