<FILEID>AP-NR-05-07-88 0229EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r p BC-DelegateList Advisory   05-07 0276</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Delegate List, Advisory,</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EDITORS</HEAD>
<HEAD>WIRE EDITORS</HEAD>
<HEAD>POLITICAL EDITORS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press today will transmit an initial list of
delegates to the Democratic National Convention July 18-21 in
Atlanta.
   This list will include information on more than 1,000 of the
4,161 delegates to the convention.
   This partial list, which is compiled by the Democratic National
Committee, contains information only on those delegates whose
selection has been certified by the party and who are not under
challenge.
   The Democratic Party will be providing weekly updates to the
delegate list, noting the addition of delegates, as well as
corrections to previous records and which delegates, if any, should
be deleted from previous lists.
   These lists will be moved as weekly installments. Because of the
overall bulk of material involved, the AP does not plan to move a
cumulative list of the delegates at some later date. Consequently,
we suggest that you make arrangements with your Saturday staff
members to save this material as it is moved.
   For each delegate, the list will give the last name, first name,
sex, race, initial presidential preference, public office title (if
any), city, state, office telephone number (if any), convention
committee assignment (if any), and delegate type (e.g.,
congressional district, automatic, at large)
   The Democratic Party is providing this material electronically
to the AP. The Republican Party has not determined whether its
computers can produce similar electronic lists for wire
transmission.
   The initial run from the Democrats is estimated to take at least
20 takes of about 1,000 words each.
   The lists will be slugged BC-Democratic Delegates-List.
   The material will begin moving late this morning on a deferred
priority.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>The AP</HEAD>
