<HEAD>Death Toll 17 In Ethnic Violence In Karachi</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death toll in nine days of ethnic
rioting rose to 17 today, despite curfews in several residential
districts.
   Police said a mechanical engineer was killed when he was caught
in cross fire between Mohajirs and Pathans battling in Shai Faisal
colony.
   Mohajirs came to India from Pakistan in 1947, and Pathans are
from Pakistan's northwest frontier province. Both compete for
scarce jobs and housing in Karachi, Pakistan's biggest city.
   Violence between the two groups erupted April 29 after a traffic
accident in which a Mohajir was killed by a Pathan driver. Since
then, police and hospital officials say 17 people have died and
more than 50 people have been injured.
