<HEAD>Two Pro-Israeli Militiamen Killed in Roadside Bomb Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Israeli-backed militiamen were killed
today in south Lebanon when a roadside bomb exploded and knocked
out their armored personnel carrier, U.N. sources in the area said.
   They said gunners of the Israeli-backed South Lebanon Army
militia responded by shelling three nearby villages, but a casualty
report was not immediately available.
   One source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the two
militiamen of the South Lebanon Army were killed on a road near the
southern village of Beit Yahon, 5{ miles north of the Israeli
border.
   The village is within Israel's self-proclaimed ``security
zone,'' a 6- to 10-mile-wide strip that Israel patrols to prevent
guerrillas from launching cross-border attacks into its northern
settlements.
