<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Storm     05-07 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Storm,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hailstorms, Heavy Rain Ravage China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Storms that raked much of China killed 21 people,
including an 8-year-old girl who was pummeled to death by
hailstones as she walked home from school, news reports said
Saturday.
   The official Xinhua News Agency said 17 of the deaths occurred
in coastal Jiangsu proince, where hailstorms and high winds damaged
or destroyed about 90,000 homes since Monday. It said 120 people
were injured in the area, while the English-language China Daily
reported injuries to 250 people in seven other provinces.
   The 8-year-old girl in Henan's Shangqui city was struck dead by
hailstones on Monday, according to China Daily. It also said 75
children were injured as they headed home, and 80 adults were also
hurt by the hailstones.
   A farmer found a hailstone weighing nearly three pounds, the
newspaper said.
   Fields in northern Anhui fields were covered by 2{ inches of
hailstones, and more than 360,000 acres of crops were destroyed,
the newspaper said.
   Up to 24 inches of rain fell on Friday and Saturday, the
official People's Daily said.
</TEXT>
