<HEAD>Australian Trying to Circle Globe in Single-Engine Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Australian pilot took off Saturday
on a bid to fly solo around the world in a single-engine airplane.
   Peter Norvill, a 37-year-old commercial pilot, wants to become
the first Australian native to make such a journey. His trip
commemorates the 200th anniversary of European settlement in
Australia.
   He took off near Sydney in a Cessna XP Hawk aircraft on a
westward route.
