<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--DirectoryDropsy     05-07 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Directory Dropsy,0174</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Missing Letters Plague Memphis Listings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   You'll have trouble finding your P's,
though not your Q's, if you use the latest edition of South Central
Bell's Memphis telephone directory.
   Some copies are missing a few names _ in the M's, N's, O's and
P's _ because a printing error dropped 73 pages.
   The books are accurate through page 338, then skip to page 411.
They run from page 411 to page 482, but the next page is 411 again.
The book continues from there to the end of the alphabet.
   Claire Bursi, a South Central Bell spokeswoman, said officials
think only 200 or so books were misprinted.
   ``When you print about 42 million directories every year, you're
bound to have a few mistakes,'' she said.
   The error was discovered Friday, shortly after distribution
began, and anyone who got a faulty directory can get a new one.
   South Central Bell's directory unit prints books for cities
throughout the Southeast, Ms. Bursi said.
</TEXT>
