<HEAD>Two Kidnapped Italian Workers Freed After Six Months</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anti-government rebels have released two
Italian technicians kidnapped six months ago, Italy's ambassador
said Saturday.
   Sudanese authorities told the embassy in Sudan that Salvatore
Barone and Paolo Bellini will arrive soon in Khartoum, where they
will be handed over to Italian officials, according to Ambassador
