<1ST_LINE>r a PM-PrecautionaryLanding     05-07 0195</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Precautionary Landing,0201</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pan Am 737 Makes Precautionary Landing Because of Smoke</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Pan American Boeing 737 airliner
made a precautionary landing at Long Beach Airport on Saturday
because smoke entered the cabin shortly after it took off from Los
Angeles International Airport, officials said.
   Flight 280 to San Diego, with 34 passengers and crew aboard,
landed safely at 7:38 a.m., said Alan Loflin, a Pan Am spokesman in
Dallas.
   There were no injuries and no damage to the plane, Loflin said.
   A small amount of smoke in the cabin was determined to come from
the ventilation system and was likely caused by some detergent that
may have gotten into a fan motor when the plane was cleaned Friday,
Loflin said.
   ``There was a presence of smoke in the cabin. It was definitely
not a smoke-filled cabin,'' Loflin said.
   The plane was scheduled to resume its flight to San Diego, he
said.
   A Federal Aviation Administration duty officer described the
landing as precautionary rather than an emergency. Loflin said
there was no emergency evacuation of the jet.
   Long Beach Airport is about 15 miles southeast of Los Angeles
International.
</TEXT>
