<HEAD>Lightning Bolt Short-Circuits Couple's Journey</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GARDEN CITY, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A lightning bolt hit a car and knocked
out its electrical system ``all at once, kaplowie,'' said a woman
riding inside.
   ``It like scared me to death,'' said Zelda Smith, who was riding
in the car driven by her husband, Lowell.
   The Smith's, from Havana, Ill., were driving Friday near the
southwest Kansas town of Garden City when they saw the storm.
   ``We noticed streaks of lightning in front of us, but it was
clearing off and we figured everything was all right,'' said Smith,
70.
   The lighting caused the couple's car to stall. It would not
restart because the bolt traveled down into the car's computer box
and knocked out the car's electrical system, Smith said.
   Smith said he and his 69-year-old wife escaped injury.
