frustrate the governor into withdrawing his opposition to raising
the speed limit to 65 mph, as 40 other states have.
   As for the governor, while he admitted that his car had gone
over the speed limit, he had nothing but nice things to say about
the state troopers who drive him.
   ``I want to just emphasize that the guys that drive me do a
superb job,'' he said. ``I don't tell them what to do. I don't
really watch them. I read the newspaper.''
