<HEAD>Judge Denies Delay in Mecham Trial</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Superior Court judge Friday refused a
two-week delay of former Gov. Evan Mecham's May 19 trial on charges
of concealing a $350,000 campaign loan.
   Defense attorney Michael Scott had asked Judge Michael D. Ryan
for the delay to give him more time to prepare and to allow an
appeals court to rule on a request for a dismissal of the charges
