   Voters got 24 hours of calm Saturday to decide who
will be their next president after a tumultuous week during which
hostages were freed in Lebanon and New Caledonia and the candidates
ended their campaigns.
   President Francois Mitterrand, 71, a Socialist seeking a second
seven-year term, remained the favorite in Sunday's runoff against
